cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SE, cs.DS, cs.CY

This paper focuses on the security of vehicular networks, specifically the distribution of Certificate Revocation Lists (CRLs) for Pseudonym Public Key Infrastructure (PPKI). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also deals with network communication and scalability, which suggests cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as a possible category. The proposed framework involves optimization and compression, which could fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper deals with privacy and identity concealment, which could be relevant to cs.CY (Computers and Society).
